<item>
            <title>[LANG-1706] ThreadUtils findThreads returns a list with nulls elements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1706</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ThreadUtils.findThreads (and other methods calling it) return a list with nulls elements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Affected version 3.13.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.12.0 works fine, not nulls elements in the returned list.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug is in findThreads method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Version 3.12.0 iterates over the Thread[] threads from 0 to count, effectively ignoring all nulls at the end of the array.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Version 3.13.0 uses Stream.of and include all null elements at the end&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve created  &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-lang/pull/1098&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Pull Request #1098&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
